2 SENATE BILL 1028
1 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “MOTORIZED VESSEL” DOES NOT INCLUDE A VESSEL
2 POWERED BY AN ELECTRIC MOTOR.
3 (B) A PERSON MAY NOT OPERATE A GASOLINE–POWERED MOTORIZED
4 VESSEL MANUFACTURED AFTER JULY 31, 2007, THAT HAS A CABIN OR OTHER
5 CLOSED LIVING SPACE ON THE WATERS OF THE STATE UNLESS THE VESSEL HAS
6 CARBON MONOXIDE WARNING LABELS AFFIXED IN CONSPICUOUS LOCATIONS IN THE
7 VICINITY OF BOTH THE TRANSOM AND THE HELM OF THE VESSEL.
8 (C) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT IMPOSE A PENALTY ON A PERSON THAT
9 VIOLATES THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SECTION.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2025.
